16/10/2009
ANKARA, Turkey -- Media reported on Thursday (October 15th) that police have arrested more than 30 suspected members of the al-Qaeda terrorist network in an operation that spanned eight provinces across the country.
The action was concentrated in the eastern provinces of Van and Erzurum, as well as in Istanbul.
The suspected are charged with planning terrorist attacks against NATO, US and Israeli targets.
They are suspected of providing logistical support to al-Qaeda camps abroad.
(Zaman - 16/10/09;
DPA, AP, Hurriyet, Anadolu news agency, Reuters - 15/10/09)
